<subSubSection id="B69203A43E519E247A84C64D3AA50E0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D9F80FDF6E8FC2E05D3BCEC5471A2EAD" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="59E9FB54FBAB3B2183C33DD7E91F228F" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Flagellar verticils 2 times length of corresponding segment. Prescutum with three dark-brown longitudinal stripes. Wing pale brown with distinct, large, brown 
<taxonomicName id="92DDCE0B370F35A5B1AACE8B648FADCE" authority="Meigen, 1818" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Trichoceridae" genus="Limnobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="stigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">stigma</taxonomicName>
; apical Sc1 slightly beyond base of Rs. Posterior margin of tergite 9 broadly emarginated. Paramere ending at 5/6 of aedeagus. Female, hypogynial valve 3.7 times longer than wide at base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F849E9187B168F0CB5528C708F2C297C" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="E5C317A6C71E223D10E72B1246117FA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6995D47B16FC88BEFA8AF51D876B7EE7" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="608AC9B0BC559439BB0D700F507A96C5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Male</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="08F7A0C5906DFAC6AB338FE100D27BC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">n</emphasis>
= 10): body length 7-9 mm, wing length 8-9.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A85EA3764EB80C2903D987FDD36CF6BA" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="D547072E243A0B6D2CA2CD651E3C33FD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Head</emphasis>
mostly dark brown (Figs 
<figureCitation id="F34FAF261FD952BED863ACA1C106614A" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E6E092E5D5753EEADAF90D71F4875219" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">7</figureCitation>
). Vertex dark brown. Occiput dull yellow. Head with black setulae. Antenna dark brown and 14-segmented; pedicel oval; flagellomeres pale brown, nearly cylindrical; flagellar verticils black, 2 times longer than corresponding segment. Rostrum and nasus brown to dark brown. Nasus 3/5 as long as rostrum. Labella pale yellow except inner margin brown, with black setulae. Palpi black brown with black setulae, terminal two segments pale brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33B736E5DB9722ADA6CCCF1D50410DA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="548866044B0E1A4FEAE132C24D421C00" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Thorax</emphasis>
mostly brown (Figs 
<figureCitation id="BF678738B568E4A326A5B9DAE52228B1" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2D0941295508BF126B301CFDC755EF89" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2</figureCitation>
). Cervical sclerite brown with black outer margin. Pronotum dull brown with black setulae. Prescutum with three dark-brown longitudinal stripes, median one with black setulae at outer margin. Scutum dark brown with black setulae at postero-lateral margin. Scutellum brown with tapered yellow median stripe. Mediotergite dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DE3909FC47EDC39C14D05DB1E4914F4B" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2</figureCitation>
). Mesopleura yellow to dark brown; subspiracular sclerite dull brown with pale-yellow spot at postero-lateral corner; episternum pale yellow to dark brown; katepisternum with black setulae and tapering, dark-brown marking at antero-lateral corner. Legs with coxae, trochanters yellow to pale brown except fore coxa yellow to dark brown; femora brown with one dark-brown, subapical ring; tibia brown; tarsi reddish brown to dark brown. Setulae on legs black. Wing hyaline, pale brown with large brown 
<taxonomicName id="ABCA3D7DF33FEF42A8A2380F4D85B4F2" authority="Meigen, 1818" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Trichoceridae" genus="Limnobia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="stigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigma">stigma</taxonomicName>
at branching of R1+2; apical Sc1 slightly beyond base of Rs, Sc2 apically reaching 1/5 of Rs; basal deflection of CuA1 before branching point of M (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DC75837B3BF2904AD99EB911A2D40A3D" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">3</figureCitation>
). Halter: stem dull brown; knob bicolor, upper part pale brown to dark brown, lower part white (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="95DD8F98964DC148983EE5F8BDF20B75" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="ED9A6FF57018BEB3F2B26684E8D237F2" doi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" start="Figures 1–3" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="19CEA3851D56B8480D272A297A850AC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="DE05CF8CB474219C9EE84A092789FDAE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Figures 1-3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5CB034C8F850CF86AA9BE70AB7512883" baseAuthorityName="Schummel" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limonia macrostigma" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostigma">
<emphasis id="2F1EEE8622069C731E486BF1761E6E12" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Limonia macrostigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male 
<emphasis id="D0A444478A901824B1C6CA2A83E8EC99" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">1</emphasis>
habitus, lateral view 
<emphasis id="5F60784438C077CF25091E823F1FE9E0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">2</emphasis>
head and thorax, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="F828EF7D8A2556ABA9BA9488DCC2B2CE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">3</emphasis>
right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="612550A7212305C57175B37D45633A85" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="E9151EA341892E0CA9E354F475661B40" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EB61B93E790C7B98ACA34418A1A551A0" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Limonia macrostigma, male 1 habitus, lateral view 2 head and thorax, dorsal view 3 right wing. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456132" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">1</figureCitation>
). Mainly dull brown. Each abdominal segment with one pale yellow ring at posterior margin. Abdomen covered with golden setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A06211ABBECC77C8A98DEE6EA87DC6A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="0908E714B6459443E9BA4AF90A1F8CE4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Hypopygium</emphasis>
dull brown (Figs 
<figureCitation id="1A218E510B2BA34B7BEA902BF82AF2A7" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4-7</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of tergite 9 broadly emarginated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0B9363C4869E8040DFDD64CED389453E" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite weakly constricted at apex. Gonostylus with apex sharp, base swollen (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4206EF3E0E544C0EF4EDF6C9AA304BE7" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0F03E2A768A7221EF5B3E930C787E56A" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">5</figureCitation>
). Paramere with fan-shaped base, very slender apex ending at 5/6 of aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation id="4A95C669B1749FF81CBF882DB57BAC2C" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4-7</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus forked; ventral mid-protrusion along middle line (Figs 
<figureCitation id="DFBB4F69CEB17B1E87835750EC2E15E4" captionStart="Figures 4–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 4 - 7. Limonia macrostigma, male 4 hypopygium, dorsal view 5 hypopygium, ventral view 6 hypopygium, lateral view 7 Aedeagus and paramere. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.971.35875.figures4-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/456133" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">4-7</figureCitation>
